ChemLeung MCQ Platform is a React + Vite web application for practicing chemistry multiple-choice questions through several different practice modes, including:

Timed practice
Marathon practice
AI-based daily mission / spaced repetition style practice
Mistake review
Custom practice
A “Millionaire” game-style mode
Tech Stack
Frontend: React (functional components + hooks), Vite
Routing: React Router v6
Styling: Tailwind CSS utilities + custom CSS (src/index.css)
Animations: Framer Motion (notably used for the mode carousel UI)
Icons: lucide-react
Backend / Data: Firebase (Auth + Firestore) integration in client code
Internationalization (i18n): A custom language context providing:
t(key) for normal translations
tf(key, params) for parameterized translations
Located in src/contexts/LanguageContext.jsx
Route Structure (high-level)
/dashboard for the main landing area
/practice for selecting practice modes (carousel UI)
/quiz for standard quiz flow
/millionaire for the Millionaire mode gameplay
/login, /register for authentication
Important Files (where to modify things)
App routing: src/App_Final.jsx
Header navigation: src/components/Header.jsx
Practice mode carousel UI: src/components/FisheyeCarousel.jsx
Practice selection page: src/pages/PracticeModeSelection.jsx
Millionaire gameplay UI/overlays: src/pages/MillionaireQuiz.jsx
Translations: src/contexts/LanguageContext.jsx
Global/custom styling: src/index.css